.\outputs\codex_findings\m7_review\codex_stdout.log:4497:outputs\codex_findings\full_audit_pass_16\findings.md:44:The remaining false positives are therefore narrower than pass 15: no social, market-research, professional-society tool, truncated-title, PubMed title-only, policy, or tech source is being promoted as T1 in this cycle. Guard 1 is visible on truncated journal titles such as the MDPI tirzepatide source, now T4 via `R10_journal_domain_truncated_title_demoted` at `clinical_tirzepatide_t2dm/live_corpus_dump.json:20`; guard 3 is visible on the ACC DOAC dosing PDF, now T3 via `R10_society_tool_demoted` at `clinical_afib_anticoagulation/live_corpus_dump.json:119`.
